[{"id":"VR444859","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\" style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of a hill. The hill has two peaks and one low point that is between the two peaks. A point P is indicated at the low point. A circle is drawn such that point P is indicated at the lowest point on the circle. A cart of mass m is shown toward the top of the hill to the left of point P.\" height=\"123\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR444859.g04.png\" width=\"325\" /></div>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A cart of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> rolls past the circular bottom of a hill (point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>P</mi></math></span></span>). Which of the following statements about the normal force <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub n\"><math alttext=\"F sub n\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math></span></span> exerted on the cart at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>P</mi></math></span></span> is correct?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR444859_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub n equals m g\"><math alttext=\"F sub n equals m g\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></math></span></span>, because the normal force on an incline is equal to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m g times the cosine of theta\"><math alttext=\"m g times the cosine of theta\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mspace width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mi>cos</mi><mspace width=\"0.1em\"></mspace><mi>θ</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta equals 0\"><math alttext=\"theta equals 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></span></span> at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>P</mi></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub n equals m g\"><math alttext=\"F sub n equals m g\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></math></span></span>, because the speed of the cart is neither increasing nor decreasing at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>P</mi></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub n\"><math alttext=\"F sub n\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math></span></span> is equal to the centripetal force on the cart at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>P</mi></math></span></span>, because only the track can exert a force toward the center of the circle.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub n\"><math alttext=\"F sub n\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math></span></span> is greater than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m g\"><math alttext=\"m g\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></math></span></span> at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>P</mi></math></span></span>, because the cart is experiencing an upward acceleration.</p>"],"answer":3}]